8 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to schools; creating the Binocular
Vision Screening Program to identify certain eye
10 disorders of students in kindergarten, first, or
third grades; directing State Department of Education
11 to administer program in consultation with the State
Department of Health; defining term; requiring
12 schools to provide comprehensive binocular vision
screenings to students; requiring screenings to be
13 conducted by trained personnel; clarifying the
binocular screenings are in addition to others
14 required; creating the Binocular Screening Revolving
Fund; designating a department to administer fund;
15 specifying source of funds and expenditures from
fund; providing procedures for payment of
16 expenditures; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
17
18
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1210.286 of Title 70, unless
23 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24
HB3016 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 A. The State Department of Education, in consultation with the
2 State Department of Health, shall establish a two-year pilot program
3 known as the Binocular Vision Screening Program, for schools to
4 offer vision screenings to students in kindergarten, first, and
5 third grades that are designed to identify convergence insufficiency
6 disorders. "Convergence insufficiency" means a vision disorder
7 characterized by a decreased ability to converge the eyes and
8 maintain binocular fusion while focusing on a near target.
9 B. Beginning with the 2026-2027 school year, the program shall
10 require schools to provide all students in kindergarten, first, and
11 third grades with a comprehensive binocular vision screening within
12 thirty (30) days of the start of the school year.
13 C. The screening required in subsection B of this section shall
14 be performed by school nurses, vision therapists, or optometric
15 technicians who are specifically trained to administer and interpret
16 results of a comprehensive binocular screening.
17 D. The screenings required by this section shall be in addition
18 to the screenings required in Section 5-148.2 of Title 70 of the
19 Oklahoma Statutes.
20 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1210.287 of Title 70, unless
22 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
24 fund for the State Department of Education to be designated the
HB3016 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 "Bin ocular Screening Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a
2 continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall
3 consist of all monies received by the State Department of Education
4 from monies appropriated or apportioned by the Legislature. All
5 monies accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby appropriated
6 and may be budgeted and expended by the State Department of
7 Education for the purpose of establishing and maintaining the
8 program created in Section 1 of this act. Monies in the Binocular
9 Screening Revolving Fund shall supplement and not supplant existing
10 school vision screening funding.
11 B. Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon warrants
12 issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by
13 law with the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
14 Services for approval and payment.
15 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
16
